#subtitle: Building relations with the other political parties of Sordland.

= Inter-Party Relationships

The <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">PFJP</span> cannot govern by itself yet. Because we do not have an electoral majority, we need the support of other parties. With the increasing pluralism in Sordland, coalition building is more common both at the local and national level. We can reach out and build additional connections with these parties, or perhaps we can stand alone.

- @independents: Strengthen our bonds with the <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> and <span style="color: #D3C24D;">bludish</span> independent MPs.
- @wpb: Strengthen our bonds with the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">Workers' Party of Bludia</span>.
- @cps: Work towards repairing relationships with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Communist Party</span>.
- @pfjp_alone: The <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">PFJP</span> can stand alone for now.
- @easy_discard


